content:
Validators cannot be identical to tests.

The result of Test 3 should be 0 4.

Add a test with a negative number.

The "Constraints" section is for constraints on the input. The puzzle explicitly expects inputs <0 and >1000.

Replace "False" with a more descriptive message.

So one of the two could add itself and mine won't ? 
2 is now good.

‚ùå Rejected the contribution.
Comment: 1. There are two existing clashes on multiplicative persistence:
https://www.codingame.com/contribute/view/1540888a5119f8f87cf3fde647912fde02bc
https://www.codingame.com/contribute/view/30243a8fd725c26bcc0ccc25a4da5dcd95a4f

2. "Special rules" (rules when "False" should be output) are not defined. Also, I don't understand why "special rules" should apply to 100,000.

Duplicates do slip through, and that should be avoided. Also, your clash suffers from a number of issues, as pointed out by @selenae above. If those can be fixed, formatting is applied (see https://www.codingame.com/playgrounds/40701/help-center/statement ) and all unnecessary special rules are removed, I may consider withdrawing my rejection.
